switchamba (0.1.3-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Fix Double-Ctrl swallowing one word on each repeated press. The
    post-paste clipboard restore raced the focused app's async paste
    and replaced the corrected text in the clipboard with the
    previous (often stale) content before the app finished reading
    it — so the app pasted the prior clipboard over the selection,
    effectively deleting a word. Remove the clipboard-restore step;
    corrected text now stays in the clipboard after the operation.
  * Slightly bump clipboard settle delays (clear/select/copy) to
    reduce Wayland clipboard races; improve Double-Ctrl logging.

 -- Vovkes <shepherdvovkes@gmail.com>  Fri, 17 Apr 2026 19:30:00 +0300

switchamba (0.1.2-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Fix trailing space being eaten after word correction: replay the
    word and its trigger boundary key in a single UInput session so
    the boundary isn't lost to the open/close race between two
    separate UInput instances.
  * Fix user keystrokes being swallowed when correction outlasts the
    suppress window: the reader now routes every key-down to the
    pending buffer while devices are grabbed, not only while within
    _suppress_until. Includes SPACE/ENTER/TAB and edit keys so they
    are replayed after ungrab instead of being silently dropped.

 -- Vovkes <shepherdvovkes@gmail.com>  Fri, 17 Apr 2026 14:00:00 +0300

switchamba (0.1.1-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Grab keyboard during word correction so user keys typed mid-replay
    are queued and flushed after, preventing interleaved output.
  * Preserve and restore user's clipboard across Double-Ctrl line
    correction; clear it first to avoid empty-selection fallback to
    prior clipboard content.
  * Add LayoutSwitcher.clear_clipboard and split write_clipboard from
    write_clipboard_and_paste.

 -- Vovkes <shepherdvovkes@gmail.com>  Fri, 17 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0300

switchamba (0.1.0-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
